added.title: Sheep Bears
added.description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

added.title: Ice Bear's Pet
added.description: Ice Bear attempts to keep a giant owl-monster secretly as a pet.

added.title: Dragon Pests
added.description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

added.title: No Land, All Air!
added.description: The Bears find themselves in a world of dog fighting planes and floating airships.

added.title: Tooth Fairy Tech
added.description: In order to earn enough money to buy a house, the Bears work as tooth fairies.

added.title: The Bad Guy Busters
added.description: Izzy wants to play a superhero game and is willing to do whatever it takes to get the others to see it through.

added.title: That's a Wrap
added.description: Duncan goes on a mission to scare Courtney during a field trip to the museum.

added.title: Tiger Fail
added.description: Gwen refuses to be pressured into choosing an ice cream flavor that she does not want.

added.title: A Ninjustice to Harold
added.description: Harold's world is turned upside down when Beth becomes the class ninja.

added.title: Having the Timeout of Our Lives
added.description: Owen forms a special bond with Duncan after having loads of fun with him during their timeouts.

added.title: This One Goes to 11
added.description: During one last stop by a toy store before Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max's maiden voyage across the Atlantic, Ben runs into an old bully, Kevin 11, who now has new powers. He's able to transform into aliens just like Ben, such as the bootleg doppelganger of Cannonbolt. Wreckingbolt!

added.title: Rath of Con
added.description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.

added.title: Poles Apart
added.description: A trip to the South Pole goes upside down when Team Tennyson lands on the North Pole instead, but Ben quickly discovers the culprits: Solar & Polar Twain, magnetically-powered scientists who want to hold the world ransom by threatening to reverse Earth's magnetic poles!

added.title: Show Don't Tell
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max arrive at a Native American national park to witness the Ayasha Plinths, an ancient Stonehenge-like rock formation. But when the sinister sorcerer Hex arrives, Ben must battle against a beast Hex magically made out of huge rocks!

added.title: Welcome to Zombozo-Zone!
added.description: During medieval times, Team Tennyson must fight to remember that they're not in the past at all, but actually at a Renaissance-esque faire, where "King Zombozo" has hypnotized its guests into thinking they live in the past!

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: I Am Okino
added.description: Inside one of the game zones, a Samurai named Okino faces a crisis of faith when he repeatedly fails to lead a series of Masters to victory, causing him to lose all hope, until some familiar ninja arrive.

added.title: The Glitch
added.description: In order to stop Unagami the ninja must obtain three Key-tanas, the first of which is hidden in the game zone Terra Kerana, one of Prime Empire's most dangerous game environments.

added.title: The Cliffs of Hysteria
added.description: While being chased by Unagami's dreaded Red Visors the ninja must climb the 'Cliffs of Hysteria', however, they make a startling discovery: Unagami is converting players into energy cubes in order to build a portal into the real world!

added.title: The Maze of the Red Dragon
added.description: Still in the game zone Terra Kerana, the Samurai guide Okino has to choose between helping his allies the ninja, or obeying the evil orders of his Master, Unagami.

added.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
added.description: When the ninja learn that the only way to acquire the second Key-tana is by winning a dangerous race in Terra Technica they'll have to find some racing cars in unexpected ways.

added.title: Dangerous Dealings/The Hunter Returns
added.description: Dangerous Dealings: The Awesome Brawler's have become aware of a growing number of adults with illegal Baku-brawling devices. But where are they all coming from? Shun decides to take things into his own hands and sets up a "sting" operation to try to draw out the person selling the devices./The Hunter Returns: Lightning has been caught and locked up by an overly aggressive dog catcher! And to make things worse, he doesn't have his collar with Baku-balls. At the compound where he's being held, he runs into an old foe.  It's up to these two enemies to team up and escape their captor.

added.title: Farewell, Phantom Thief
added.description: After being exposed as a phantom thief in the Bakugan battle league, the Awesome Brawlers are concerned about Ajit, but have no idea of his whereabouts. Dan is particularly affected by Ajit's disappearance and sets out to find him to get some answers./Ajit is out to set right all the wrong doings of his phantom thief past. When he attempts to break into a museum to return artifacts, his mentor Storm is waiting for him. A Bakugan brawl breaks out between two when Storm rolls out his new Bakugan: Cimoga.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik/First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik: It's the Haavik Show! Haavik shows up unexpectedly at the practice field and proposes he and Dan play a little game. The Awesome Brawlers have never seen this man before, but they sense something is odd about him. Regardless, when Haavik strokes Dan's ego, there's no way he's backing down from this challenge./First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous: With his back against the wall, Dan tries flipping the script on Haavik by challenging him to a game of his own - a Bakugan Brawl. If Dan wins, then Haavik will have to set him, and the other Awesome Brawler's free.

added.title: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers/The Return of Sophie
added.description: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers: The Awesome brawlers go to see Benton Dusk to tell him about the Fusion Bakugan and ask him if he knows anything about this character: Haavik. However, the meeting takes an unexpected twist when Haavik decides to crash it./The Return of Sophie: A video has surfaced showing Toshi using an illegal Baku-Brawling device! Shun has his hands full when Sophie starts making trouble for Kazami Holdings, accusing them of illegally exploiting Bakugan.

added.title: Wynton's Reality Show/Bakugan Soccer
added.description: Wynton's Reality Show: Lia has had it with Wynton's pranking, but little does she know Wynton is in for a taste of his own medicine. A prank goes too far, and Wynton finds himself in a real-life nightmare with a rampaging Bakugan!/Bakugan Soccer: The Awesome Brawlers and their Bakugan decide to have a game of Bakugan Soccer! The intensity ramps up when Pepe, his teammates and a mysterious coach show up for a little fun. It will take major teamwork for the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan to defeat this rowdy bunch.

added.title: Esto llega hasta el Once
added.description: Durante una última parada en una juguetería antes del viaje inaugural de Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max a través del Atlántico, Ben se encuentra con su antiguo bravucón, Kevin 11, que ahora tiene nuevos poderes. Es capaz de transformarse en alienígenas al igual que Ben, como el doble "pirata" de Cannonbolt: iWreckingbolt!

added.title: Convencion de Rath
added.description: De regreso en casa, Ben no puede inscribirse en un concurso de cosplay de gatos sin su propio disfraz. Pero cuando se convierte en Rath, un nuevo alienígena con aspecto felino y mal carácter, el lado salvaje que Ben acaba de descubrir pronto tendrá resultados inesperados.

added.title: Polos Opuestos
added.description: Un viaje al Polo Sur queda patas arriba cuando el equipo Tennyson aterriza en el Polo Norte. Pero Ben rápidamente descubre a los culpables: iSolar y Polar Twain, unos científicos con poder magnético que quieren chantajear al mundo amenazando con invertir los polos magnéticos de la Tierra!

added.title: No lo digas y Hazlo
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max llegan a un parque nacional nativo americano para conocer los plintos de Ayasha, una antigua formación rocosa parecida a la de Stonehenge. Pero cuando llega el siniestro hechicero Hex, iBen debe luchar contra una bestia que Hex hizo mágicamente con rocas enormes!

added.title: Bienvenido a la Zona Zombozo
added.description: Durante tiempos medievales, el equipo Tennyson debe esforzarse por recordar que no están en el pasado, sino en una feria renacentista, idonde el "Rey Zombozo" ha hipnotizado a sus invitados para que crean que viven en el pasado!

added.title: Yo Soy Okino
added.description: Dentro de una de las zonas de juego, un Samurai llamado Okino se enfrenta a una crisis de fe cuando no logra que los Maestros obtengan la victoria.

added.title: La Falla
added.description: Para detener a Unagami, los Ninjas debe obtener 3 Keytanas, la primera está escondida en Tierra Karana, uno de los entornos de juego más peligrosos.

added.title: Los Acantilados de la Histeria
added.description: Los Ninjas suben a los Acantilados de la histeria y descubren que Unagami convierte a los jugadores en cubos de energía para construir un portal.

added.title: El Laberinto del Dragon Rojo
added.description: Aún en la zona de juego de Tierra Karana, Okino tiene que elegir entre ayudar a sus aliados ninjas, u obedecer las órdenes de su Maestro, Unagami.

added.title: Un Paso Adelante, Dos Pasos Atras
added.description: La única manera de que los Ninjas obtengan segunda Keytana es ganando una carrera en Tierra Technica y tiene que conseguir autos de carreras para eso.

added.title: Los Caza Chicos Malos
added.description: Izzqy quiere jugar un juego de superhéroes y está dispuesta a hacer lo que sea por ello.

added.title: Show de momias
added.description: Duncan sale en una misión para espantar a Courtney durante una excursión al museo.

added.title: Fallo de tigre
added.description: Gwen se niega a que la presionen para elegir un sabor de helado que no quiere.

added.title: Una ninja justicia para Harold
added.description: El mundo de Harold queda de cabeza cuando sus compañeros declaran que Beth es la verdadera ninja de la clase.

added.title: El castigo de mi vida
added.description: Owen forma un nexo especial con Duncan después de que ambos se divirtieran mucho durante sus castigos.

added.title: Sidekicked to the Curb
added.description: When Bam is sent to take on Prank, Redbird is forced to hang back because The Joker's van is too dangerous! When Bam discovers that Redbird secretly tagged along, he's upset… until Redbird bails him out of a tight spot.

added.title: Keep Calm and Roll On
added.description: After Jestah's insults get the best of her, a short-tempered Bibi tries to not let the big-wheeled bully's words get to her so she can help Batgirl catch Harley.

added.title: Snow Cap
added.description: Pauleen Penguin hires The Looney Builders to build her a home in Looneyburg. Lola soon discovers they got the design wrong and the crew has to make adjustments.

added.title: Tweety-Go-Round
added.description: Tweety leads The Looney Builders in building a new merry-go-round at the park for the kids. His crane breaks down and his small size affects his ability to contribute to the build.

added.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
added.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

added.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
added.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

added.title: Bring it On Beresford
added.description: On Plant-A-Tree Day on Sodor, Thomas and Diesel both want to deliver the most impressive pine for the holiday, but they'll have to compete by delivering all the other trees first. When Thomas wins the race and the pine is loaded onto his flatcar, he discovers that he overestimated the job and himself, resulting in the tree falling in a deep ditch! Luckily, Beresford the Crane has a plan to aid the Number One Engine! Will they be able to plant the biggest tree before the end of the holiday?
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: What's in a Name?
added.description: When Cranky gets overwhelmed on a busy and blustery day at Brendam Docks, he accidentally gets Riff and Jiff's names confused, sending them on opposite deliveries. An observant Thomas hears the mistake, but does not correct the crankier-than-usual crane -- thinking, grown-ups don't make mistakes! Thomas is proven wrong, however, when he ends up at Whiff's Recycling Plant and old tires are delivered to McColl's Farm because of Cranky's error. After calming the chaos in both places, Thomas learns that it is important to speak up and tell someone they are making a mistake --- even if it is a grown-up!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Mystery Boxcars
added.description: Kana is upset when she keeps running out of power, but a mystery scavenger hunt is just the thing to cheer her up.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Super Screen Cleaners
added.description: Thomas pretends to be a hero to help ensure the movie screen Nia's delivering arrives clean and pristine.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Overnight Stop
added.description: Percy feels anxious about spending a night away from home during an overnight delivery with Thomas and Nia.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Gravity
added.description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.

added.title: Honey
added.description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

added.title: Ocean
added.description: Blippi's trusty BlippiMobile safely transports him to a whole new underwater world! He dives into the sea, where he gets an ocean tour from a local resident, Jerry the Jellyfish. They swim through a huge kelp forest, explore the ocean floor and meet interesting underwater creatures along the way!

added.title: Planets
added.description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

added.title: Mountain
added.description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

added.title: Bee a Bee dance
added.description: Come sing this song and dance with our Lellobee City Farm friends to learn how to move like a Bee! Ella, Izzy, and Lettie are having fun playing and learning about bees!

added.title: The Growing Song
added.description: Let's celebrate everything that grows with the Growing Song! Come sing along! Have you ever noticed that everything is changing? Watch the different seasons of the year and revisit plants, animals, children, and buildings in the farm and city to see how they've grown.

added.title: Wheels on the Bus
added.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

added.title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
added.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

added.title: Yes Yes Vegetables Song - Healthy Habits!
added.description: Baby Izzy doesn't like vegetables - until they sing a song with her!

added.title: The Sandman Is Coming
added.description: Daffy thinks the Sandman is a monster that throws sand in children's eyes.

added.title: Some Assembly Required
added.description: Bugs gets a new toy with assembly required and has to learn to follow instructions.

added.title: All Washed Up
added.description: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath.

added.title: Did Not! Did Too!
added.description: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

added.title: Tea & Basketball
added.description: Sylvester wants to play tea with the girls while Lola wants to play basketball with the boys.
